---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Low-Light Plant Placement Checklist"
  description="A checklist for deciding whether an apartment spot can support low-light houseplants without guesswork."
  canonicalPath="/low-light-plant-placement-checklist/"
  type="article"
>
  <article class="content">
    <p class="eyebrow">Checklist</p>
    <h1>Low-Light Plant Placement Checklist</h1>
    <p class="lede">Use this before buying a plant for a hallway, shelf, bedroom corner, or windowless-looking room.</p>
    <h2>Pass or fail checks</h2>
    <table>
      <thead><tr><th>Check</th><th>Pass</th><th>Fail</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Sky visibility</td><td>You can see sky from the plant spot</td><td>No sky visible from the spot</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Reading test</td><td>You can read small print without a lamp at midday</td><td>You need a lamp during daytime</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Distance</td><td>Within 8 ft of a window</td><td>Across a room, behind a wall, or in a hallway</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Plant type</td><td>Known tolerant foliage plant</td><td>Flowering, variegated, succulent, or herb</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h2>Decision tree</h2>
    <ol>
      <li>If no daylight reaches the spot, use a grow light or choose a non-living display.</li>
      <li>If daylight is weak but present, choose ZZ plant, snake plant, cast iron plant, or pothos.</li>
      <li>If the plant stretches within a month, move it closer to glass before changing watering or fertilizer.</li>
    </ol>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
